The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, Sept. 29: The government has allowed retailers to sell to end consumers products sourced from group wholesale companies backed by foreign firms, a move that may help firms such as Bharti Wal-Mart. Issuing a new consolidated FDI policy, the industry ministry said, The change has been made in response to the request from stakeholders for simplification of the guidelines.                             
	 New Delhi, Sept. 29: Growth of core infrastructure industries slowed to 3.7 per cent in August compared with 6.4 per cent in the same month last year, according to government data.                             
	 Mumbai, Sept. 29: Market watchdog Sebi today said FIIs that had not provided detailed information on their holding structures and account holders would not be allowed to undertake fresh trading in India from October 1.                            
	 New Delhi, Sept. 29: Tata Steel has entered into an agreement with a consortium of 13 banks to raise about Rs 25,000 crore to refinance the loan it took to partly fund the acquisition of Corus.                            
	 Calcutta, Sept. 29: The government of Rajasthan has granted a prospecting lease to Hindustan Copper for Baniwali Ki-Dhani. The lease area is located near HCLs existing unit at Khetri Nagar.
                                                                                                                          
